The article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama designating May 7, 2009, as the National Day of Prayer. The proclamation highlights the historical significance of prayer in times of challenge and unity in American history, such as during the Continental Congress and the Civil War. The proclamation also emphasizes the importance of honoring the service and sacrifice of the United States Armed Forces and promoting peace and goodwill among people of different beliefs. The proclamation is in accordance with the Public Law 100-307, which calls on the President to issue such a proclamation each year.